    img = img / 2 + 0.5
    npimg = img.numpy()
    plt.imshow(np.transpose(npimg, (1, 2, 0)))

def modify_model(model, last_layers_only=True, device="cpu"):
    #    
    work_model = model.to(device)

    if last_layers_only:
        #    
        for param in work_model.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = False
        num_ftrs = work_model.fc.in_features
        work_model.fc = nn.Linear(num_ftrs, 10).to(device)  # 10   CIFAR-10
    else:
        #   
        num_ftrs = work_model.fc.in_features
        work_model.fc = nn.Linear(num_ftrs, 10).to(device)  # 10   CIFAR-10
    return work_model

def train_and_evaluate(model, trainloader, testloader, experiment_name, device, last_layers_only=True, num_epochs=5, learning_rate=0.001, momentum=0.9):
    work_model = modify_model(model, last_layers_only, device)
    print(f": {experiment_name}")

    #     
    criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()
    optimizer = optim.SGD(work_model.parameters(), lr=learning_rate, momentum=momentum)

    for epoch in range(num_epochs):
        start_time = time.time()

        #  
        work_model.train()
        running_loss = 0.0
        for inputs, labels in trainloader:
            inputs, labels = inputs.to(device), labels.to(device)
            optimizer.zero_grad()
            outputs = work_model(inputs)
            loss = criterion(outputs, labels)
            loss.backward()
            optimizer.step()
            running_loss += loss.item()

        #  
        work_model.eval()
        correct = 0
        total = 0
        with torch.no_grad():
            for inputs, labels in testloader:
                inputs, labels = inputs.to(device), labels.to(device)
                outputs = work_model(inputs)
                _, predicted = torch.max(outputs.data, 1)
                total += labels.size(0)
                correct += (predicted == labels).sum().item()

        end_time = time.time()
        epoch_time = end_time - start_time

        #     
        print(f" {epoch + 1}:  - : {running_loss / len(trainloader):.4f}  - : {100 * correct / total:.2f}%  : {epoch_time:.2f} \n")

    #   
    print(" .")
    print(f" :    ImageNet")
    print(f" : SGD, learning rate = {learning_rate}, momentum = {momentum}, num_epochs = {num_epochs}")
    print(f"     : {100 * correct / total:.2f}%\n")
    return correct / total
